# Do NOT create `deploy/stack/.env` here.
#
# Docker Compose auto-loads a file named `.env` in the same directory as the compose file. That file
# overrides `--env-file` / release pins in surprising ways. Use **repo root** `.env` only (two levels up from this directory):
#   cp ../../.env.example ../../.env
#
# If you already have `deploy/stack/.env` on a machine, delete it and keep all settings in ../../.env
#
# Author: kejiqing
